OL,7,FChief probation officer Kim Thornden-
OL,8,FEdwards said she was "deeply sorry for
OL,9,Fthe unacceptable failings" in the
OL,10,Fcase, and they were taking immediate
OL,11,Fsteps to address the issues raised in
OL,12,Fthe report.
OL,14,FThis included "increased support for
OL,15,Fnewly qualified probation officers and
OL,16,Fimproved access to substance misuse
OL,17,Ftreatment for supervised offenders
OL,18,Fwith a history of drug use," she said.
